  "response": "Here are some of the most commonly cited plot holes and flaws in Rogue One:\n\n1. CGI characters\n- The digital recreations of Grand Moff Tarkin and young Leia were criticized as distracting and uncanny valley-like\n\n2. Character development\n- Many characters felt underdeveloped or two-dimensional\n- Minimal backstory for Jyn Erso and other protagonists\n- Lack of deep character arcs\n\n3. Motivation issues\n- Jyn's sudden transformation from cynical loner to rebel hero seemed rushed\n- The motivations of some characters felt inconsistent or unclear\n\n4. Unnecessary scenes\n- Some action sequences felt superfluous or added just for spectacle\n- Saw Gerrera's character seemed underdeveloped and underutilized\n\n5. Plot convenience\n- The Rebels conveniently finding the Death Star plans\n- Some characters' survival or escape scenarios seemed implausible\n\n6. Continuity problems\n- Some minor inconsistencies with established Star Wars canon\n- Technology and character interactions that didn't perfectly align with original trilogy\n\n7. Pacing issues\n- First half of the movie felt slow and disjointed\n- Abrupt tonal shifts between different scenes and locations\n\nDespite these criticisms, many fans still appreciated the film's overall contribution to the Star Wars narrative.",
